title: Research
text:
Torrey Pine Conservation





This project has involved collecting seeds and data on the rarest pine tree in the world; Pinus torreyana ssp. insularis. On top of seed harvesting, I have been tasked with the collection of location data using GIS in order to track maternal lines. Read more here!


Plant Establishment Trials





This project is an ongoing attempt to understand how pot size and irrigation level effect the growth of several common native plant species. My main tasks are collection, analysis, and reporting of monthly data. Read more here!
